dcterms:description: This dataset contains random 3-regular graphs for a binary node classification problem. Both training and test data contain 1000 graphs. The training graphs have 20 nodes, and test graphs have 20 nodes for the normal dataset and 100 nodes for the extrapolation dataset. A node v is positive if v has two neighboring nodes that are adjacent to each other.
dcterms:title: TRIANGLE

dcterms:creator: D. J. Watts
S. H. Strogatz
dcterms:description: This dataset contains random 3-regular graphs for a multi-label node classification problem. Both training and test data contain 1000 graphs. The training graphs have 20 nodes, and test graphs have 20 nodes for the normal dataset and 100 nodes for the extrapolation dataset. The class of node v is the local clustering coefficient of v.
dcterms:title: LCC

dcterms:creator: L. Becchetti
P. Boldi
C. Castillo
A. Gionis
dcterms:description: MUTAG is a chemical compound dataset where each node represents an atom and each edge represents a chemical bond. Graphs are labelled according to their mutagenic effect on a bacterium.
dcterms:title: MUTAG

dcterms:creator: L. Becchetti
P. Boldi
C. Castillo
A. Gionis
dcterms:description: NCI1 is a chemical compound dataset where each node represents an atom and each edge represents a chemical bond. Graphs are labelled according to the bioassay records for anti-cancer screen tests with non-small cell lung.
dcterms:title: NCI1

dcterms:creator: L. Becchetti
P. Boldi
C. Castillo
A. Gionis
dcterms:description: PROTEINS is a protein dataset where each node represents a secondary structure element, and a node feature vector is a one-hot vector that represents a structure type (helix, sheet, or turn). Graphs are labelled according to whether they are enzymes or non-enzymes.
dcterms:title: PROTEINS
